segue into the theme.

06:13.173 --> 06:14.673
Or i could start
with the title,

06:14.675 --> 06:15.741
And then we could both
segue into the theme.

06:15.743 --> 06:17.676
Welcome, everyone,

06:17.678 --> 06:19.978
To our very first
glee club rehearsal.

06:23.217 --> 06:25.817
First, i would like to welcome
back our distinguished alumni

06:25.819 --> 06:28.253
Who have so graciously agreed
to stay an extra week.

06:28.255 --> 06:29.755
So, thank you, thank you,
thank you.

06:29.757 --> 06:31.723
Yeah, how exactly are you guys
doing that?

06:31.725 --> 06:33.392
Oh, i can bend time
and space with my mind.

06:33.394 --> 06:36.194
Okay, so, as you very
well have heard,

06:36.196 --> 06:38.497
The glee club has a grand
and glorious tradition

06:38.499 --> 06:40.065
Of starting each
week with a lesson

06:40.067 --> 06:43.034
Where we explore every
musical genre under the sun.

06:43.036 --> 06:44.836
But mostly katy perry
and show tunes.

06:44.838 --> 06:47.773
Not this week. Rachel and i
are extremely excited

06:47.775 --> 06:49.508
To kick off this week's
lesson with our...

06:49.510 --> 06:53.845
First musical lesson,
"jagged little tapestry."

06:53.847 --> 06:56.715
Oh, look, finally some songs
about rachel's hair extensions.

06:56.717 --> 06:59.251
Now, as you can clearly see,
we've combined the titles

06:59.253 --> 07:01.353
Of these two
iconic albums...

07:01.355 --> 07:03.889
Alanis morissette's
<i>jagged little pill.</i>

07:03.891 --> 07:07.793
Which is celebrating its
20th-year anniversary.

07:07.795 --> 07:09.461
And carole king's
<i>tapestry.</i>

07:09.463 --> 07:11.396
That-that's my favorite.

07:11.398 --> 07:14.199
So these two iconic
albums are sort of

07:14.201 --> 07:15.534
Like chocolate and
peanut butter.

07:15.536 --> 07:17.035
Both...
Or peanut butter
and jelly.

07:17.037 --> 07:19.738
Okay, they're both different
but amazing.

07:19.740 --> 07:21.306
You know, you could say
that they're sort of

07:21.308 --> 07:22.908
Like the reese's
pieces of music.
Mm-hmm.

07:22.910 --> 07:24.876
Right?
Or, if you don't
like reese's pieces,

07:24.878 --> 07:27.779
You could name another
candy of your choice.

07:29.917 --> 07:32.951
Okay, kurt, why
don't you now...

07:32.953 --> 07:34.653
Well-well, carole king's
<i>tapestry</i> is-is...

07:34.655 --> 07:36.421
You know,
it's easy and informal,

07:36.423 --> 07:38.623
Like you're getting a cup
of coffee with an old friend.

07:38.625 --> 07:41.059
Both:
Team carole.

07:41.061 --> 07:42.127
Good choice.

07:42.129 --> 07:43.995
Okay, and alanis
is different.

07:43.997 --> 07:45.897
You know, she's edgy
and dark...
Angry.

07:45.899 --> 07:47.833
Team alanis.

07:47.835 --> 07:51.069
Yeah, and this is why we wanted
it to be your first lesson.

07:51.071 --> 07:52.337
Because, like
alanis and carole,

07:52.339 --> 07:53.672
You can look at every situation

07:53.674 --> 07:55.574
From two different
points of view, you know?

07:55.576 --> 07:57.609
It's about
combining...
I think what kurt
is trying to say is

07:57.611 --> 07:59.744
That it's about working together
and using this lesson

07:59.746 --> 08:01.012
To grow as a team.

08:01.014 --> 08:02.581
I'm sorry, i'm confused.

08:02.583 --> 08:04.816
What is it exactly
you want us to do?

08:04.818 --> 08:07.452
Just sit and smile like
i did for three years.

08:07.454 --> 08:09.287
So, our weekly lesson
is to find a partner

08:09.289 --> 08:11.456
That has a different style
than you and work together

08:11.458 --> 08:14.259
To mash up an alanis
and a carole song.

08:14.261 --> 08:15.527
Kurt and i will demonstrate...

08:15.529 --> 08:17.963
Probably tomorrow?
What? We...

08:17.965 --> 08:20.198
(quietly):
Let me tell you something--
why do you keep interrupting me?

08:20.200 --> 08:22.334
You're interrupting me,
and you're confusing them.

08:22.336 --> 08:23.935
You're confusing the
hell out of them.

08:23.937 --> 08:26.271
Santana: Okay, or how about
since you and porcelain

08:26.273 --> 08:28.273
Obviously have some issues
to iron out,

08:28.275 --> 08:30.075
Brittany and i will go first.

08:30.944 --> 08:32.177
Thank you.
Okay, thank you.

08:32.179 --> 08:33.678
That'd be great.
(school bell ringing)

08:33.680 --> 08:34.946
Quinn, can i talk
to you for a sec?

08:34.948 --> 08:36.381
Artie told me
that you said

08:36.383 --> 08:37.716
That brown was not
an ivy league school.

08:37.718 --> 08:38.984
That's not what i said.

08:38.986 --> 08:40.852
I said it's barely
an ivy league school.

08:40.854 --> 08:42.153
Becky.

08:42.155 --> 08:43.688
(groans)

08:43.690 --> 08:44.890
I thought you were in college.

08:44.892 --> 08:46.191
I am, idiot.

08:46.193 --> 08:48.360
I came back because
i'm in trouble.

08:48.362 --> 08:49.494
I need help.

08:49.496 --> 08:50.629
I met a guy
named darrell,

08:50.631 --> 08:53.164
And now he's my boyfriend.

08:53.166 --> 08:54.966
And i'm madly
in love.

08:54.968 --> 08:56.067
Well, that's amazing.

08:56.069 --> 08:57.369
Shut up! I know!

08:57.371 --> 08:58.570
I brought him home

08:58.572 --> 09:01.206
To lima
so he can meet my parents.

09:01.208 --> 09:02.240
Okay, so what's the problem?

09:02.242 --> 09:04.142
Bitch! The problem is

09:04.144 --> 09:05.310
That i lied to him.

09:05.312 --> 09:06.978
I told darrell
that i was

09:06.980 --> 09:09.981
The president of every club
at school.

09:09.983 --> 09:12.484
¶ ¶

09:20.661 --> 09:23.428
Becky, that's
an insane web of lies.

09:23.430 --> 09:24.829
I know, whore.

09:24.831 --> 09:26.865
But that's not
the worst part.

09:26.867 --> 09:29.034
I told him
that i was in glee club.

09:29.036 --> 09:31.202
Wait, why would you
tell him that?

09:31.204 --> 09:33.438
Because he was in glee club
in high school,

09:33.440 --> 09:36.408
And i want to impress him
by my singing voice.

09:36.410 --> 09:38.843
You got to let me sing
at the glee club

09:38.845 --> 09:40.946
When darrell comes
to school tomorrow.

09:40.948 --> 09:42.180
Becky, we will do

09:42.182 --> 09:43.615
Whatever it takes to help you.

09:43.617 --> 09:44.983
Thanks, kitty.

09:46.420 --> 09:48.920
(sighs)
you know, i am pretty sure

09:48.922 --> 09:51.890
That our fish ancestors
crawled out of the ooze

09:51.892 --> 09:53.892
And got legs just
to be able to scissor.

09:53.894 --> 09:55.460
Well, actually,

09:55.462 --> 09:57.295
Scissoring was invented
by the ancient egyptians,

09:57.297 --> 09:59.431
Which is weird because actual
scissors weren't invented

09:59.433 --> 10:01.733
For many centuries
after that. True story.

10:01.735 --> 10:03.401
(chuckles)
you know,

10:03.403 --> 10:05.370
I have to say,
i'm kind of really digging this

10:05.372 --> 10:07.472
Back-to-the-future
for glee club.

10:07.474 --> 10:09.808
If for no other reason
than to mess

10:09.810 --> 10:12.310
With berry and her sad gay.

10:12.312 --> 10:15.614
But i have
the perfect mash-up idea

10:15.616 --> 10:17.115
For us to perform
this week.

10:17.117 --> 10:18.917
So do i. Okay, you go first.

10:18.919 --> 10:20.552
Three, two, one.

10:20.554 --> 10:22.320
"i feel the earth move"
and "hand in my pocket."

10:22.322 --> 10:23.421
"you oughta know."

10:23.423 --> 10:24.723
No, see, you're supposed to do

10:24.725 --> 10:26.591
A song from each album.

10:26.593 --> 10:28.760
Okay, but i refuse to be
restrained by the laws of man.

10:28.762 --> 10:30.629
I like to think
outside of the box.

10:30.631 --> 10:32.263
No, listen. Okay.

10:32.265 --> 10:35.567
Aren't we here to help
the glee club get back on top?

10:35.569 --> 10:37.235
And don't you think
that teaching the power

10:37.237 --> 10:39.604
Of a mash-up would
totally contribute to that?

10:39.606 --> 10:41.806
Okay, i may be a genius, but...

10:41.808 --> 10:45.377
How can i argue with the logic
of your giant, generous heart?

10:46.313 --> 10:47.746
Come here.

10:50.817 --> 10:52.917
Ugh, we are so awesomely
in love.

10:52.919 --> 10:55.820
I would totally hate us
if i didn't know us.
I was thinking.

10:55.822 --> 10:58.690
I think that you and i should
live in new york together.

10:58.692 --> 11:01.292
You know? I-i want to go back
to college-- nyu

11:01.294 --> 11:03.361
Or columbia--
and you can just go...

11:03.363 --> 11:05.964
Wherever i get in, genius.

11:05.966 --> 11:07.866
How much fun would it be

11:07.868 --> 11:09.134
To be back in school
together again?

11:09.136 --> 11:10.101
(sighs) it'd be amazing!

11:10.103 --> 11:11.836
I love you, britt.

11:11.838 --> 11:13.872
I love you, too.

11:13.874 --> 11:15.607
I'm serious. I mean...

11:15.609 --> 11:17.042
Living my life with you is

11:17.044 --> 11:18.877
One of the few things
that's actually

11:18.879 --> 11:22.113
As good in real life
as it is in my imagination.

11:22.115 --> 11:23.615
Like raining phones.

11:23.617 --> 11:26.785
(laughs)
exactly.

11:26.787 --> 11:28.453
I'm serious.

11:28.455 --> 11:31.623
You make me so happy.

11:31.625 --> 11:34.492
And i'm never going to
stop doing just that.

11:34.494 --> 11:37.062
As a math genius, i am
one of the few people

11:37.064 --> 11:39.164
Who understands the
concept of infinity,

11:39.166 --> 11:43.401
And i will love you until
infinity, santana lopez.

11:45.305 --> 11:48.239
And i will love you
until infinity, too, britt.

11:54.481 --> 11:55.647
(school bell ringing)

11:55.649 --> 11:57.248
Sue: Oh, becky,
there's no way

11:57.250 --> 11:59.651
This wouldn't impress
that new boyfriend of yours.

11:59.653 --> 12:03.254
